==English==

===Noun===
'''frown'''

# A facial expression in which the corners of the mouth are turned downward, usually indicating [[displeasure]] or [[disapproval]].

====Translations====
*Bosnian:[[namrštiti se]]
*Finnish: [[otsa]]n [[rypistys]], [[vihainen]] [[katse]]
*German: [[finster]]er [[Blick]]
*Spanish: [[ceño]] {{m}}

===Intransitive verb===
'''frown''' ([[frowned]], frowned)

# To have a frown on one's face.
# To express disapproval. (''Society frowns on fraud and theft.'')

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[rypistää]] [[otsaansa]] (1), [[paheksua]] (2)
*French: raler
*German: [[finster]] [[dreinblicken]] (1), [[missbilligen]] (2)

